you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view stryker corporation  wikipedia stryker corporation from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search stryker corporation type public traded as nyse syk sp  component industry medical technology founded  founder homer stryker headquarters kalamazoo michigan usa key people john w brown – chairman emeritus kevin a lobo – president  chief executive officer products medical devices orthopaedic implants surgical equipment neurovascular products patient handling and emergency medical equipment revenue  billion usd  operating income  billion usd  number of employees approx   website wwwstrykercom stryker corporation nyse syk is a fortune  medical technologies firm based in kalamazoo michigan strykers products include implants used in joint replacement and trauma surgeries surgical equipment and surgical navigation systems endoscopic and communications systems patient handling and emergency medical equipment neurosurgical neurovascular and spinal devices as well as other medical device products used in a variety of medical specialties in the united states most of strykers products are marketed directly to doctors hospitals and other healthcare facilities internationally stryker products are sold in over  countries through companyowned sales subsidiaries and branches as well as thirdparty dealers and distributors contents  business segments  history  john brown  corporate governance  recent acquisitions  –  –today  acquisition history  sponsorships  regulatory controversies  references  external links business segmentsedit stryker segregates their reporting into three reportable business segments orthopedics medical and surgical medsurg and neurotechnology and spine orthopedics products consist primarily of implants used in hip and knee joint replacements and trauma and extremities surgeries medsurg products include surgical equipment and surgical navigation systems instruments endoscopic and communications systems endoscopy patient handling and emergency medical equipment medical and reprocessed and remanufactured medical devices as well as other medical device products used in a variety of medical specialties stryker neurotechnology and spine products include a portfolio of products including both neurosurgical and neurovascular devices their neurotechnology offering includes products used for minimally invasive endovascular techniques as well as a line of products for traditional brain and open skull base surgical procedures orthobiologic and biosurgery products including synthetic bone grafts and vertebral augmentation products as well as minimally invasive products for the treatment of acute ischemic and hemorrhagic stroke stryker also develops manufactures and markets spinal implant products including cervical thoracolumbar and interbody systems used in spinal injury deformity and degenerative therapies historyedit the orthopedic frame company the precursor of stryker corporation was formed on february   by dr homer stryker a kalamazoo michigan orthopedist stryker developed the turning frame a mobile hospital bed that allowed for repositioning of injured patients while providing necessary body immobility the cast cutter a cast cutting apparatus that removed cast material without damaging underlying tissues and the walking heel among others in  the company name was officially changed to stryker corporation in  stryker made an initial public offering of stock and later acquired osteonics corporation entering the replacement hip knee and other orthopedic implants market stryker in  annual sales reached  billion and in  stryker was included in the sp  and the forbes platinum  for the first time in  sales reached  billion and stryker was listed in the fortune  for the first time in  stephen p macmillan joined stryker as president and ceo in  annual sales reached  billion and john w brown transitioned to the single role of chairman of the board a role he retired from in  while steve macmillan became president  ceo by  stryker sold its physiotherapy associates division to private equity firm water street healthcare partners for  million in february  mr macmillan resigned and curt r hartman was named interim chief executive officer and vice president and chief financial officer mr william u parfet was named nonexecutive chairman of the board on october   mr kevin a lobo was appointed as president and chief executive officer at the end of  stryker had approximately  global employees and annual sales of  billion  of those sales were outside the us stryker rollinstretcher in a  global market overview of top medical technology firms stryker was ranked number  with total portfolio sales in excess of  billion moreover the firm maintains  worldwide reconstructive market share  worldwide medsurg market share  worldwide neurotechnology and spine market share the company was recognized by hermann simon as a role model for other small to mediumsized business in his book hidden champions john brownedit brown served as president ceo and finally chairman of the board across a year career with stryker one report attributes strykers rise from a maker of hospital beds to a worldclass medical technology company to brown as of update browns retained investment in stryker placed him on the forbes  list with a net worth of us corporate governanceedit as of  members of the board of directors of stryker corporation are kevin a lobo chairman president  ceo william u parfet lead independent director howard e cox jr srikant m datar phd dr roch doliveux louise l francesconi allan c golston andrew silvernail ronda e stryker recent acquisitionsedit –edit in  stryker purchased howmedica the orthopaedic division of pfizer for  billion howmedica became stryker orthopaedics in au