r general this litigation called for a net payout of  million as the governmental department maintains the aforementioned companies engaged in unlawful kickbacks to physicians who urged hospitals to purchase their respective products stryker however having cooperated early in the investigation was not fined as of february  a dispute exists between stryker corp and the us department of justice concerning a subpoena linking the company to aforementioned misconduct in sale of products since governmental filing of the injunction stryker notes that it has produced in excess of  pages of documentation in compliance with the mandate us government counters however that the documentation was not proper in scope and format law officials expect the investigation to continue for several months stryker recalled several models of medical vacuums sold under the neptune waste management system brand in june and september  the devices some of which had not been cleared by the food and drug administration caused a fatal accident when the vacuum was mistakenly used to suction a passive drainage tube referencesedit   stryker  k filing february   part  item   lamiman kevin stryker corporation better investing  november  –  a b c d staff october    john brown the forbes  forbes print    owen katherine a and yin becker fact book  investor relations public affairs  media relations stryker corporation  may  httpphxcorporateirnetexternalfileitemugfyzwsuqmtgnjafenoawxksuqltfvhlwztzt  simon hermann hidden champions of the st century  success strategies of unknown world market leaders london springer  isbn   stryker board of directors stryker corporation  october  httpwwwstrykercomenuscorporateforinvestorscorporategovernanceboardofdirectorsindexhtm  press releases stryker corporation  october  httpphxcorporateirnetphoenixzhtmlcpirolnews  george john  may  orthovita to be bought by medical technology giant stryker philadelphia business journal american city business journals retrieved  may     j